<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content container">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>Colgate-Palmolive (CL) Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <div class="header-desc">A transparent, step-by-step discounted cash flow valuation using FY2025 actuals.</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ VERDICT CARD ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="vc-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value</div>
    <div class="vc-value">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
    <div class="vc-price">Current Price: ${currentPrice.toFixed(2)} | Margin of Safety: {marginOfSafety}%</div>
    <div class="vc-status" style={`color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY & ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology & Assumptions</h2>
  <p>This valuation uses a two-stage Discounted Cash Flow (DCF) model. We take Colgate-Palmolive's actual FY2025 Free Cash Flow, project it forward for 5 years based on estimated growth, calculate a terminal value for all cash flows thereafter, and discount everything back to today's dollars.</p>

  <div class="assumptions-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Base FCF (FY2025)</div>
      <div class="card-value">${(fcf2025 / 1000).toFixed(2)}B</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Actual free cash flow generated in FY2025. This is our starting point.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="card-value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(0)}%</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Projected annual FCF growth for the next 5 years. Based on stable consumer goods growth.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Terminal Growth</div>
      <div class="card-value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Growth rate into perpetuity. Capped at global GDP growth estimates.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Discount Rate</div>
      <div class="card-value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(0)}%</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Required rate of return. Based on the 10-year Treasury (4.18%) plus a risk premium suited for its low beta (0.264).</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
  <h2>1. Cash Flow Projections (Years 1-5)</h2>
  <p>Here is the math for the next 5 years. We apply the {(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(0)}% growth rate to the base FCF, then discount it back to present value using the {(discountRate * 100).toFixed(0)}% discount rate.</p>

  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
          <th>Projected FCF</th>
          <th>Discount Factor</th>
          <th>Present Value</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {projectedFCF.map(p => (
          <tr>
            <td class="row-header">Year {p.year}</td>
            <td>${p.fcf.toLocaleString()}M</td>
            <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(3)}</td>
            <td class="highlight-cell">${p.pvFCF.toLocaleString()}M</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td class="row-header">Sum of PV (Phase 1)</td>
          <td></td>
          <td></td>
          <td>${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}M</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ TERMINAL VALUE ═══ -->
  <h2>2. Terminal Value</h2>
  <p>Colgate-Palmolive won't stop operating after 5 years. The terminal value accounts for all cash flows from Year 6 into eternity, assuming a mature growth rate of {(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%.</p>

  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="row-header">Year 6 FCF (Year 5 × 1.025)</td>
          <td>${Math.round(fcfYear6).toLocaleString()}M</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="row-header">Terminal Value (Gordon Growth)</td>
          <td>${terminalValue.toLocaleString()}M</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td class="row-header">Present Value of Terminal Value</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}M</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ ENTERPRISE TO EQUITY VALUE ═══ -->
  <h2>3. From Enterprise to Equity Value</h2>
  <p>Adding the present value of Phase 1 and the Terminal Value gives us the <strong>Enterprise Value</strong> (the value of the core business operations). To find what the equity (shares) is worth, we must add the company's cash and subtract its debt.</p>

  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="row-header">PV of Phase 1 Cash Flows</td>
          <td>${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}M</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="row-header">+ PV of Terminal Value</td>
          <td>${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}M</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td class="row-header">Enterprise Value</td>
          <td>${enterpriseValue.toLocaleString()}M</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="row-header">+ Cash & Equivalents</td>
          <td>${cashAndInvestments.toLocaleString()}M</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="row-header">- Total Debt</td>
          <td>${totalDebt.toLocaleString()}M</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td class="row-header">Equity Value (Market Cap Equivalent)</td>
          <td>${equityValue.toLocaleString()}M</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="row-header">÷ Shares Outstanding</td>
          <td>{sharesOutstanding}M</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td class="row-header">Intrinsic Value Per Share</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ HISTORICAL CHARTS ═══ -->
  <h2>Financial Track Record</h2>
  <p>Before trusting a forward projection, look at where the company has been. Here's Colgate-Palmolive's 5-year performance.</p>

  <h3>Revenue ($B)</h3>
  <div class="bar-chart">
    {revenueHistory.map(r => (
      <div class="bar-row">
        <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
        <div class="bar-track">
          <div class="bar-fill revenue" style={`width: ${(r.value / 20382) * 100}%`}>
            ${(r.value / 1000).toFixed(1)}B
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>

  <h3>Free Cash Flow ($B)</h3>
  <div class="bar-chart">
    {fcfHistory.map(r => (
      <div class="bar-row">
        <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
        <div class="bar-track">
          <div class="bar-fill fcf" style={`width: ${(r.value / 3634) * 100}%`}>
            ${(r.value / 1000).toFixed(1)}B
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>

  <h3>Earnings Per Share (Diluted)</h3>
  <div class="bar-chart">
